它做出了那个举动，<ins> <a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/twitters-apps-are-breaking-following-elon-musks-decision-to-cap-tweet-rates-125028807.html">破坏了各种 Twitter 应用程序，</a></ins> “检测并消除损害平台的机器人和其他不良行为者”，例如那些正在抓取数据来训练人工智能模型的人。 Twitter 补充说，当时速率限制影响了一小部分用户。</p><p> Twitter 不再设有可供置评的通讯部门。尽管如此，公共推文再次可供任何人查看，就像 Meta 一样<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/metas-threads-is-already-showing-conversations-on-the-web-120453471.html">开始推出</a></ins>它的 Twitter 竞争对手是 Threads。该服务预计将在多个市场上线<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/metas-instagram-linked-twitter-rival-threads-could-arrive-on-july-6th-063129168.html">星期四</a></ins>， 但<ins><a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/metas-twitter-rival-threads-wont-initially-launch-in-the-eu-090314803.html">不在欧盟。</a></ins></p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/twitter-quietly-backtracks-on-requiring-users-to-log-in-to-see-tweets-135230558.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/twitter-quietly-backtracks-on-requiring-users-to-log-in-to-see-tweets-135230558.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 7f8ab664-d44b-49ff-8ace-0a8aaf037b50</guid><dc:creator>克里斯·霍尔特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Wed, 05 Jul 2023 13:52:30 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688565151</ingested><modified> 2023-07-05T13:52:33+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[Social & Online Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Kris Holt]]></category><media:content height="2665" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-01/3